<br>
Until recently, beastlords had a level buffing spell that they used on their pets.  They would summon a green pet, and then buff the level.  They also have haste, sow, etc.<br>
<br>
Using Puppet Strings, a friend of mine used to charm a YK in WC, buff the level of it to 48th level or so, sow it, buff it, etc.  And then zone...<br>
<br>
Here you had this enraged bear, buffed to hell and gone, rampaging around WC.  Newbies screaming for help, training it to the druid rings, higher levels deciding to &quot;help out the poor lowbie&quot; and getting their butt handed to them because they didn't expect a YK to be dangerous.  OMG, it was funny. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eumerin>Eumerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 6:11:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Funniest ever</span><hr size=1> Not pet/mage related, but two things that I did hear last night.<br>
First was in PoK, where I hear someone auctioning to sell mana vials (the ones enchanters make for tradeskills) as a way to increase mana regen.  A few of us tried to provide friendly corrections for the auctioneer, but the auctioneer started claiming that the vials really did work as claimed, and that 'hundreds of satisfied customers' could vouch for them.<br>
Uh-huh.  Right...<br>
<br>
The other one was more amusing.  Someone in Nexus asked if the Centi Shortsword could be equipped in the secondary slot.  A couple of other people said yes.  Then the original person asked why they couldn't equip it.  I figured it was a clueless knight class character, so I did a /who.<br>
Level 1 rogue.<br>
Gee, I wonder...<br>
