<br>
However, one story of little people sticks out in my mind. I was level 52 and returning to Felwithe to finally see what that retarded Paladin in the mage guild had as a quest. I'd wondered that for close to 40 levels, although I was always too lazy or forgetful to look it up.<br>
<br>
Nevertheless, I scour vendors like mad whenever I go into a town. No telling what turns up on those things for insanely cheap prices!<br>
<br>
So I turned into a small little shoppe by the Cleric/Pally guild, and there were two newbies...Level 3 each. But wonder of wonders, they were ACTUALLY role playing.<br>
<br>
Me being a HUGE fan of Roleplaying, I simply could not resist. One was a Wood Elf Ranger, and the other a High Elf Wizard. I was floating on cash at the time (how rare)...So to the Ranger I gave a Sword of Skyfire, and to the Wizard I gave a Blackened Crystalline Robe.<br>
<br>
They were so excited and so polite to receive them, and it was just a touching little memory that I have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calebe>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 591<br> <font color=#333333>(1/1/03 9:49:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ....</span><hr size=1> On the good side of new players, I remember when I was level 34 or so and back in my home city of Qeynos and saw a level 4 magician. He had nothing but his newbie robe and summoned dagger.<br>
<br>
This was way before Kunark was even thought of. I have him a staff of Writhering. He thanked me and I thought from time to time I wonder whatever happened to that mage and the staff. I didn't write the name down etc.. just gave it and gated out.<br>
<br>
Fast forward to  Kunark and Skyfire. I am now level 55, and always hunting in an all magician group. We have this same group going on for a few weeks when on of them says to me.<br>
<br>
You may not remember me, but I do you. You gave me a Staff of Writhering in Qeynos. He went on to say that was the first time someone ever gave his character anything, and remembered my name all this time.<br>
<br>
He told m at first he was scared of the staff as the effect &quot;Chaotic Feedback&quot; had him scared I was trying to trick him <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but he soon learned and used that staff a long time, when he told me he passed it to another new non twinked Magician with the instructions to pass it down to the next new magician he saw when he out grew. Sadly that Mage (Fryersyker) left our server shortly there after, but I wonder still if that original Staff of Writhering is still making the round in my server. I really hope it is.<br>
